右
Right.

350
00:39:47,322 --> 00:39:48,365
左
Left.

351
00:39:53,829 --> 00:39:54,871
右
Right.

352
00:39:58,750 --> 00:40:00,001
打直
Hang a Louie.

353
00:40:03,130 --> 00:40:04,506
拉掣阀
Toss a Ritchie.

354
00:40:07,884 --> 00:40:09,553
拉手
Port astern.

355
00:40:11,722 --> 00:40:13,557
放慢
To the starboard.

356
00:40:14,850 --> 00:40:17,436
- 我的拖鞋
- 你的车票要掉了
-My slipper.
-You're gonna lose your ticket.

357
00:40:17,602 --> 00:40:19,479
不是我的,是你的
It's not my ticket, it's yours.

358
00:40:19,646 --> 00:40:21,481
- 我的?
- 对!
-It's my ticket?.
-Yes.

359
00:40:21,648 --> 00:40:23,775
右…跟着我…左…
Right. Keep up with me. Left.

360
00:40:24,109 --> 00:40:26,528
右…左…
Right. Left.

361
00:40:30,574 --> 00:40:31,908
右…
Right.

362
00:40:32,242 --> 00:40:33,535
左…
Left.

363
00:40:33,702 --> 00:40:35,078
右…
Right.

364
00:40:35,245 --> 00:40:37,205
左…右
Left. Right.

365
00:40:40,917 --> 00:40:42,210
- 噢，糟糕！
- 噢，糟糕！
-Oh, no!
-Oh, no!

366
00:40:44,421 --> 00:40:46,256
抓紧了
Brace yourselces!

367
00:40:57,225 --> 00:40:59,144
呵…这才像话
Well, that's more like it.

368
00:41:01,521 --> 00:41:03,065
谢谢你
Thank you.

369
00:41:03,231 --> 00:41:06,526
谢谢你
真不敢相信,你帮我找到车票
Thank you. I can't believe
you found my ticket.

370
00:41:07,069 --> 00:41:09,696
谁说…找到…车票了?
Did someone say they found a ticket?.

371
00:41:11,698 --> 00:41:15,118
这么说…车票拿来吧
Well, in that case.... Tickets, please.

372
00:41:24,002 --> 00:41:25,545
谢谢
Thank you.

373
00:41:27,255 --> 00:41:31,176
-“L-E”?
- 和那个万事通的一样
-""L-E""?.
-Just like that know-it-all kid.

374
00:41:46,191 --> 00:41:48,777
走路小心
Watch your step.
Tricky walking up here.

375
00:41:48,944 --> 00:41:51,321
提醒你,上坡时,路很滑
It's mighty slick.
Mighty slick, I tell you.

376
00:41:52,489 --> 00:41:55,033
我刚说啥来着!?
There you go. What did I tell you?.

377
00:41:55,200 --> 00:42:00,330
很久以前
我首次圣诞夜之旅
我在车顶巡视…
Years ago, on my first Christmas Ece run,
I was up on the roof making my rounds...

378
00:42:00,497 --> 00:42:02,416
也踩到冰滑了一下
...when I slipped on the ice myself.

379
00:42:02,582 --> 00:42:06,002
我伸手去抓栏杆
但栏杆断了,就滑倒了
I reached out for a hand iron,
but it broke off. I slid and fell.

380
00:42:06,169 --> 00:42:10,173
但是没有掉下车去
And yet, I did not fall off this train.

381
00:42:10,757 --> 00:42:13,009
某人救了你?
Someone saved you?.

382
00:42:13,176 --> 00:42:15,178
也可能是某“物”
Or something.

383
00:42:18,056 --> 00:42:19,349
天使
An angel.

384
00:42:20,267 --> 00:42:21,935
或许
Maybe.

385
00:42:22,102 --> 00:42:24,187
等等…
Wait. Wait.

386
00:42:25,022 --> 00:42:28,191
他长的什么样子?
你看到他了吗?
What did he look like?. Did you see him?.

387
00:42:29,317 --> 00:42:33,196
没有,有时…眼见为实
No, sir. But sometimes
seeing is believing.

388
00:42:33,572 --> 00:42:38,702
有时…最真实的我们却看不见
And sometimes the most real things
in the world are the things we can't see.

389
00:42:44,541 --> 00:42:46,877
这些被遗弃的
The forsaken and the abandoned.

390
00:42:48,045 --> 00:42:52,049
小心走
这些可怜的玩具受了不少罪…
Mind your step, now.
These poor toys hace suffered enough...

391
00:42:52,215 --> 00:42:56,553
被世人到处抛弃,自生自灭
...being left to rust and decay in the
back alleys and cacant lots of the world.

392
00:42:57,054 --> 00:42:58,847
它们怎么会在这儿?
-What are they doing here?.
-It's a new concept the boss came up with.

393
00:42:59,014 --> 00:43:01,224
这是领导的新点子

394
00:43:01,391 --> 00:43:04,770
与其丢弃它们
不如收集起来修补一下
Instead of being thrown away,
they're collected. Refurbished.

395
00:43:05,479 --> 00:43:10,567
他说这是循环
反覆,再生什么的
He calls it ""rebicycling.""
Something like that.

396
00:43:12,819 --> 00:43:15,238
真令人伤心
Makes me wanna cry...

397
00:43:15,405 --> 00:43:18,575
看到它们这样被虐待
...seeing toys that were
treated this way.

398
00:43:19,368 --> 00:43:23,580
这些吊绳都打结的木偶问题才大
These hopelessly entangled
string puppets and marionettes...

399
00:43:23,747 --> 00:43:28,043
我们在北极处理这些玩具的人员…
...pose a particular problem. We found
the nimble fingers of our work force...

400
00:43:28,210 --> 00:43:32,547
为了打开绳结,可费尽脑筋了…
...here at the North Pole are best
for working out those knots and tangles.

401
00:43:32,714 --> 00:43:35,258
谢谢你，这里双保险
Thank you. Double-locked here.

402
00:43:46,645 --> 00:43:50,107
朋友,你就像我一样…
You are just like me, my friend.

403
00:43:50,273 --> 00:43:52,651
一个捣蛋鬼
A scrooge!

404
00:43:52,818 --> 00:43:54,986
埃比尼泽捣蛋鬼
Ebenezer Scrooge.

405
00:43:55,153 --> 00:43:58,490
捣蛋鬼从来不信什么…
North Pole, Santa Claus, this train...

406
00:43:58,657 --> 00:44:02,577
圣诞节,北极,圣诞老人…等等
全是难以置信,骗人的玩意儿
...it's all a bunch of humbug.
A bout of indigestion.

407
00:44:02,744 --> 00:44:05,330
喔,我是到你是啥…
Oh, yeah. I know what you are.

408
00:44:05,497 --> 00:44:08,125
你是个“怀疑论”者
You're a doubter.

409
00:44:08,291 --> 00:44:10,836
你怀疑,你不相信…
A doubter. You don't believe!

410
00:44:11,002 --> 00:44:14,172
你是怀疑论者! 你不相信
You're a doubter! You don't beliece!

411
00:44:31,273 --> 00:44:34,192
你错过好戏啦
我们爬过陡坡
You missed it.
We rode down some really sharp hills.

412
00:44:34,359 --> 00:44:36,403
然后经过似乎结冰的湖面
We were on what looked like a frozen lake.
But I know it was just an optical illusion.

413
00:44:36,570 --> 00:44:38,739
但是我说是视觉假像

414
00:44:38,905 --> 00:44:41,825
他说车子是走在冰上
我说这不可能…
He said the train was on ice.
I said it's impossible--

415
00:44:41,992 --> 00:44:44,661
因为车轨不可能…
你去哪里?
You can't put a train track--
Where you going now?.

416
00:44:59,217 --> 00:45:02,179
# 我对星星许愿 #
I'm wishing on a star

417
00:45:02,345 --> 00:45:05,515
# 试着去相信 #
And trying to believe

418
00:45:05,682 --> 00:45:08,852
# 虽然很遥远 #
That even though it's far

419
00:45:09,311 --> 00:45:11,855
# 但确有圣诞夜 #
He'll find me Christmas Eve

420
00:45:12,481 --> 00:45:15,609
# 我猜圣诞老人很忙 #
I guess that Santa 's busy

421
00:45:15,776 --> 00:45:18,779
# 因为他从未来过 #
'Cause he's never come around

422
00:45:19,279 --> 00:45:25,035
# 圣诞节来临时,我就会想到他 #
I think of him
When Christmas comes to town

423
00:45:25,827 --> 00:45:28,997
# 那是一年中最好的时光 #
The best time of the year

424
00:45:29,164 --> 00:45:32,376
# 所有的人都回家了 #
When everyone comes home

425
00:45:32,542 --> 00:45:35,712
# 在圣诞节的气氛下 #
With all this Christmas cheer

426
00:45:35,879 --> 00:45:39,424
# 是不该独自渡过的 #
It's hard to be alone

427
00:45:39,591 --> 00:45:45,639
# 朋友们都聚在一起竖起了圣诞树 #
Putting up the Christmas tree
With friends who come around

428
00:45:45,806 --> 00:45:52,187
# 圣诞节来时,真是有趣 #
It's so much fun
When Christmas comes to town

429
00:45:52,979 --> 00:45:59,069
# 孩子们的礼物包五颜六色 #
Presents for the children
Wrapped in red and green

430
00:45:59,611 --> 00:46:05,409
# 这些我都听过,却没见过 #
All the things I've heard about
But never really seen

431
00:46:06,243 --> 00:46:08,745
# 圣诞夜没人会睡觉 #
No one will be sleeping

432
00:46:08,912 --> 00:46:11,998
# 圣诞夜的晚上 #
On the night of Christmas Eve

433
00:46:12,165 --> 00:46:19,256
# 翘首盼望圣诞老人降临 #
Hoping Santa 's on his way

434
00:46:19,423 --> 00:46:22,509
# 当他雪橇上的铃声响起 #
When Santa 's sleighbells ring

435
00:46:22,676 --> 00:46:25,554
# 我仔细听 #
I listen all around

436
00:46:25,721 --> 00:46:28,932
# 当天使唱起圣歌 #
The herald angels sing

437
00:46:29,099 --> 00:46:32,102
# 我却从来都听不见 #
I never hear a sound

438
00:46:32,644 --> 00:46:36,106
# 孩子们的其他梦想 #
And all the dreams of children

439
00:46:36,273 --> 00:46:39,067
# 曾逝去的会再寻回 #
Once lost will all be found

440
00:46:39,234 --> 00:46:45,157
# 当圣诞来时，这就是我所有的祈望 #
That's all I want
When Christmas comes to town

441
00:46:47,534 --> 00:46:56,209
# 当圣诞来时
这就是我所有的祈望 #
That's all I want
When Christmas comes to town

442
00:47:07,721 --> 00:47:09,181
看呀
Look.

443
00:47:11,850 --> 00:47:13,852
北极光
The northern lights.

444
00:47:16,688 --> 00:47:18,732
喂,你们叁个
Hey. You three.

445
00:47:19,941 --> 00:47:21,735
我们刚经过…
We just crossed it.

446
00:47:21,902 --> 00:47:27,324
北纬66度33分…北极圈
Latitude 6622'.
The Arctic Circle.

447
00:47:27,491 --> 00:47:30,827
你们看到远方的极光吗?
And do you see?.
Those lights in the distance.

448
00:47:31,745 --> 00:47:36,208
看起来像大货船航行在
结冰的海上所发出奇异的光芒
They look like the lights of a strange
ocean liner sailing on a frozen sea.

449
00:47:37,501 --> 00:47:39,503
那…
There...

450
00:47:40,170 --> 00:47:42,214
就是北极
...is the North Pole.

451
00:47:47,219 --> 00:47:50,055
地上有魔毯
从来没有休息过
It's a magic carpet on a rail
It never takes a rest

452
00:47:50,222 --> 00:47:53,392
飞过高山和白雪
flying through
The mountains and the snow

453
00:47:53,558 --> 00:47:56,520
只要你愿意
就可以免费加入，享受快乐
You can ride for free and join the fun
If you just say yes

454
00:47:56,687 --> 00:48:00,023
在极地特快上
事情就是这样子的
'Cause that's the way things happen
On the Polar Express

455
00:48:00,190 --> 00:48:03,318
呜~呜~汽笛响
是她唱歌的声音
Whoo, whoo, the whistle blows
That's the sound of her singing

456
00:48:03,485 --> 00:48:06,697
叮~叮~铃声响
天哪，看着她走
Ding, ding, the bell will ring
Golly, look at her go

457
00:48:06,863 --> 00:48:09,866
你觉得如果我们很快到达
谁来猜一猜…
You wonder if you'll get there soon
Anybody's guess

458
00:48:10,033 --> 00:48:13,245
在极地特快上
事情就是这样子的
'Cause that's the way things happen
On the Polar Express

459
00:48:13,412 --> 00:48:16,540
当我们到那里
就会尖叫，“噢，耶”
When we get there
We'll scream, ""Yay!""

460
00:48:16,707 --> 00:48:19,042
我们到达那里
附和着邦~邦~邦
We'll arrive with
A bang, bang, bang

461
00:48:19,209 --> 00:48:22,212
还有噗~噗~噗
路上一直说笑着
Boom, boom, boom
Laughing all the way

462
00:48:27,217 --> 00:48:30,137
到了! 比预定时间
还早5分钟!
We made it. With fice minutes to spare.

463
00:48:30,303 --> 00:48:32,180
到了!
We made it.

464
00:48:57,622 --> 00:48:59,916
精灵呢? 他们在哪儿?
There should be elces.
Where are the elces?.

465
00:49:00,083 --> 00:49:01,752
对呀,精灵在哪儿?
Yeah, where are the elces?.

466
00:49:01,918 --> 00:49:04,254
他们都聚集在市中心
They are gathering
in the center of the city.

467
00:49:04,421 --> 00:49:08,216
圣诞老人就在那儿
给出圣诞节的第一个礼物
That is where Santa will give
the first gift of Christmas.

468
00:49:09,092 --> 00:49:11,553
谁会拿到圣诞节的第一个礼物?
Who gets the first gift of Christmas?.

469
00:49:11,720 --> 00:49:15,599
他会在你们之中…选一个
He will choose one of you.

470
00:49:18,643 --> 00:49:21,605
- 看!
- 精灵!
-Look.
-Elces!

471
00:49:52,469 --> 00:49:54,805
听好咯…听好咯…先生女士们
All right. All right,
ladies and gentlemen.

472
00:49:54,971 --> 00:49:57,683
请大家排成两队
Two columns, if you please.

473
00:49:57,849 --> 00:50:00,644
矮的排前面,高的排后面
Shorter in the front, taller in the rear.

474
00:50:01,144 --> 00:50:04,773
偶数生日在右边,奇数生日在左边
Even-numbered birthdays on the right,
odd-numbered on the left.

475
00:50:04,940 --> 00:50:07,859
不可以推人,不要到处闲逛
No pushing. No pushing.
But let's not dilly-dally.

476
00:50:08,026 --> 00:50:09,945
还有5分钟才到午夜
It's fice minutes to midnight.

477
00:50:10,112 --> 00:50:13,699
怎么算的呀!
4分钟前也是剩5分钟!
Hey, what gives?. It was five minutes
till midnight four minutes ago.

478
00:50:14,157 --> 00:50:16,660
没错! 排成两排…
Exactly. Columns of two.

479
00:50:16,827 --> 00:50:18,954
- 一排…两排
- 对不起
-One, two.
-Excuse me.

480
00:50:19,121 --> 00:50:21,581
- 有问题吗?
- 他怎么办?
-Question.
-What about him?.

481
00:50:24,334 --> 00:50:27,045
没人会被强迫去见圣诞老人
No one is required to see Santa.

482
00:50:28,171 --> 00:50:31,383
先生女士们,你们不需要牵手
Ladies and gentlemen,
you do not hace to hold hands...

483
00:50:31,550 --> 00:50:35,011
- 快点!
- 走的过程中…
-Come on.
-...but please remain in your columns...

484
00:50:35,178 --> 00:50:37,556
请不要离开队伍…
...while we are in transit.

485
00:50:47,190 --> 00:50:50,694
- 你必须跟我们走
- 她说的对
-Look, you have to come with us.
-She's right.

486
00:50:52,612 --> 00:50:57,075
我从来信不圣诞节
Christmas just doesn't work out
for me. Never has.

487
00:50:57,242 --> 00:50:59,870
但是圣诞节是多么美好的时光
But Christmas is such a wonderful,
beautiful time.

488
00:51:00,037 --> 00:51:03,665
和朋友家人享受施与受的感恩
It's a time for giving and being thankful,
for friends and family.

489
00:51:03,832 --> 00:51:08,628
大家用饰品和灯来装饰圣诞树
圣诞老人也会把礼物留在树下
People hang decorations and lights. Santa
leaces presents under our Christmas trees.

490
00:51:10,547 --> 00:51:12,299
只是我…
Christmas just...

491
00:51:12,883 --> 00:51:14,760
从来信不圣诞节
...doesn't work out for me.

492
00:51:16,553 --> 00:51:20,265
听着…我不管你信不信圣诞节
Look, I don't know if Christmas
is gonna work out for you or not...

493
00:51:20,432 --> 00:51:23,560
今晚是圣诞夜,不要独自一人
...but this is Christmas Eve.
Don't stay here by yourself.

494
00:51:25,228 --> 00:51:26,772
对,跟我们走
Yes, come with us.

495
00:51:27,314 --> 00:51:29,107
我们一起去
We'll go together.

496
00:51:41,203 --> 00:51:42,829
不好
Oh, no.

497
00:51:50,879 --> 00:51:52,756
我们会平安无事
We're gonna be okay.

498
00:51:55,092 --> 00:51:57,219
或许不会!
Maybe not!

499
00:51:59,096 --> 00:52:01,056
紧急刹车!
The emergency brake.

500
00:52:01,223 --> 00:52:03,183
紧急刹车!
The emergency brake.

501
00:52:06,895 --> 00:52:10,691
没有刹车…我找不到刹车
There's no brake. I can't find the brake!

502
00:52:17,197 --> 00:52:19,783
休息会儿吧,孩子
Take a break, kid.

503
00:52:19,950 --> 00:52:23,620
热巧克力咖啡怎么样?
How about a nice, good hot cup of Joe?.

504
00:52:52,232 --> 00:52:53,316
快要撞上了！
We're gonna crash!

505
00:53:00,323 --> 00:53:02,242
我们在转圈圈
We're spinning.

506
00:53:28,018 --> 00:53:29,978
嘘…你们听到了吗?
You hear that?.

507
00:53:30,562 --> 00:53:31,855
铃声
The bell.

508
00:53:33,231 --> 00:53:35,609
- 什么铃声?
- 雪橇上的铃声
-What bell?.
-The sleighbell.

509
00:53:35,776 --> 00:53:38,195
- 雪橇上的铃声?
- 听到了吗?
-Sleighbell?.
-Don't you hear it?.

510
00:53:39,529 --> 00:53:42,074
从隧道那边来的
It's coming from that tunnel.

511
00:53:47,621 --> 00:53:49,748
我们该朝那边去
That's the way we should go.

512
00:53:58,215 --> 00:53:59,758
快呀
Come on.

513
00:54:31,957 --> 00:54:33,542
怎么啦?
What?.

514
00:54:34,042 --> 00:54:36,712
- 怎么啦?
- 快点
-What?.
-Come on.

515
00:54:48,682 --> 00:54:49,725
快点
Come on.

516
00:54:59,526 --> 00:55:01,319
我们迷路了
We're lost.

517
00:55:11,288 --> 00:55:12,706
是的
Yes.

518
00:55:13,957 --> 00:55:16,877
- 是…我听到了
- 我也听到了
-Yes. I hear it.
-I hear it too.

519
00:55:17,044 --> 00:55:21,131
- 我什么也没听到
- 是那边来的声音
-I don't hear anything.
-Okay, it's down this way.

520
00:55:21,298 --> 00:55:22,507
你确定?
Are you sure?.

521
00:55:27,095 --> 00:55:28,430
非常确定
Absolutely.

522
